1. Ctrl-Left moves cursor by arg;
2. Ctrl+U deletes entire line;
3. Ctrl+R then "nano" allows search recent commands includes "nano";
4. Tab for autocomplete;
5. sudo !! adds sudo to last command you run;
6. if you type 'napa' instead of 'nano', use ^nanp^nano to correct last line;
7. "history | grep nano" calls out recent command line number includes nano, then ! number to run it again;
8. use {} to expand arg;
9. more to add.
